Modifications by Dinesh Palaniswamy / NetApp SecLab include:

- OpenAI Responses API (/v1/responses) native implementation with SSE parser,
  WebSocket transport layer (dormant), bidirectional Gemini converter, request
  pipeline, compaction client, and full type definitions (~3,100 lines)
- 4-layer context management: tool output masking service, pre-flight context
  budget trimming (Anthropic + OpenAI), dynamic token tracking, enhanced
  compaction with structured XML state_snapshot prompt
- Parallel read-only tool execution
- JIT (just-in-time) context injection system
- read_many_files batch file reading tool
- Omission placeholder detector (blocks lazy model code generation)
- Resilient subagent tool rejection with contextual feedback
- SSL/TLS and network retry resilience
- History immutability enforcement via readonly types
- Token display enhancement (color-coded thresholds, compaction proximity)
- Null space fixes in Gemini lingua franca conversion (Responses reasoning
  round-trip, Anthropic redacted_thinking preservation, tool_result.is_error)
- Model support additions (Claude Opus 4.6 1M context, adaptive thinking,
  DeepSeek R1, auto-detect max_tokens)
- APEX enterprise distribution (SEA binary, npm package, MCP server bundling,
  branded CLI with /rca and /testplan commands)
- Integration test suite against NetApp LiteLLM proxy
